16/09/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Transportation Minister Binali Yildirim on Wednesday (15 September) dismissed the chief of the state railway company TCDD, Suleyman Karaman, and his deputy Kemal Ergulec, following allegations of mismanagement and three deadly train accidents in the past two months. 
Karaman was the highest-ranking cabinet official involved in a trial stemming from the three incidents, which killed 60 people and injured dozens. 
(NTV - 16/09/04; AP - 15/09/04)
